{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "Execute Test Scripts",
  "description": "Executes all YAML test scripts in e2e-tests/ folder against the running emulator/simulator (Android and/or iOS), takes screenshots at every assertion, and generates an Excel (.xlsx) report with test steps, coverage metrics, and requirement traceability.",
  "version": "2",
  "when": {
    "type": "userTriggered"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "First ensure openpyxl is installed: run 'pip3 install openpyxl' if not already available. Then: 0) Call mobile_list_available_devices to detect ALL available devices (Android and iOS). For EACH online device whose platform matches the test script's platform field, run the full test suite. PLATFORM-SPECIFIC BEHAVIOR: For Android: use ADB text input (~/Library/Android/sdk/platform-tools/adb -s {device_id} shell input text) for typing, use mobile_press_button BACK to dismiss keyboard, disable stylus with 'adb shell settings put secure stylus_handwriting_enabled 0' if needed. For iOS: use mobile_type_keys for text input (works reliably on iOS), dismiss keyboard by tapping outside field or pressing Done, use swipe-right from left edge for back navigation (no BACK button on iOS), handle system permission alerts by tapping Allow/Don't Allow. Then read all YAML test script files in e2e-tests/ folder. For each script: 1) Check if current device platform matches the script's platform field — skip if not compatible. 2) Launch the app fresh (terminate + relaunch). 3) Execute each step (tap, type, swipe, assert, clear) using mobile-mcp tools with platform-appropriate methods. 4) On 'clear' action: Android use ADB KEYCODE_CTRL_A + KEYCODE_DEL; iOS use triple-tap to select all then type replacement. 5) On assert steps, verify the condition using mobile_list_elements_on_screen. 6) Create run folder with format: e2e-runs/run-{DD-MM-YY}_(HH-MM)/ using current date and time. 7) Take screenshot after every assertion — save directly to e2e-runs/run-{DD-MM-YY}_(HH-MM)/screenshots/ with naming convention e2e-{platform}-{test-number}-{test-name}-{pass|FAIL}.png. 8) If assertion fails, screenshot immediately and continue. After all scripts are executed on all devices: 9) Generate e2e-test-report.xlsx (Excel) in that run folder with columns: User Flow, Test No., Test Scenario, Test Steps (numbered), Expected Results, Status (Passed/Failed/Skip with color coding), Actual Results (if Passed: same as Expected; if Failed: what actually happened), Screenshot (filename). If multiple platforms tested, group by platform or add a Platform column. Use openpyxl. Include metadata header (app name, device(s), date, pass/fail summary). 10) Generate metadata.yaml in that run folder with date, device info (all devices tested), TC version, pass/fail counts per platform. Follow the report-excel and baseline-integration steering file formats. Report to user: run folder name, pass/fail count per platform, and path to the Excel report."
  }
}